20for%20cooling,%20storage,%20incorporating%20in%20products,%20growing%20crops).%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EIn%20the%20context%20of%20this%20Standard,%20suppliers%20with%20significant%20water-related%20impacts%20may%20include%20suppliers%20of%20water-intensive%20commodities%20or%20services,%20suppliers%20located%20in%20areas%20with%20water%20stress,%20and/or%20suppliers%20with%20significant%20impacts%20on%20the%20local%20water%20environment%20and%20the%20related%20local%20communities.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EIf%20applicable,%20the%20organization%20can%20describe%20its%20environmental%20impacts%20caused%20by%20runoff,%20and%20how%20they%20are%20addressed.%20For%20example,%20runoff%20can%20carry%20high-%20nutrient%20and%20pollution%20loads%20due%20to%20the%20organization&amp;rsquo;s%20activities,%20leading%20to%20eutrophication%20and%20other%20negative%20impacts%20on%20local%20waterbodies.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20Guidance%20for%20Disclosure%20303-1-b%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EWhen%20assessing%20impacts,%20it%20is%20important%20that%20the%20organization%20consider%20its%20future%20impacts%20on%20water%20quality%20and%20availability,%20as%20these%20factors%20can%20change%20over%20time.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3ETools%20and%20methodologies%20for%20identifying%20impacts%20can%20include%20life%20cycle%20assessments,%20environmental%20impact%20assessments,%20water%20footprint%20assessments,%20scenario%20analysis,%20and%20stakeholder%20engagement.%20If%20information%20is%20estimated%20or%20modeled,%20rather%20than%20sourced%20from%20direct%20measurements,%20the%20organization%20can%20explain%20its%20estimation%20or%20modeling%20methods.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20Guidance%20for%20Disclosure%20303-1-c%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EWorking%20with%20stakeholders%20is%20critical%20for%20an%20organization%20to%20steward%20water%20as%20a%20shared%20resource%20and%20account%20for%20the%20needs%