ty%20sourcing%20that%20comes%20from%20catchments%20located%20in%20areas%20with%20water%20stress.%20The%20organization&amp;nbsp;is%20encouraged%20to%20include%20information%20about%20upstream%20as%20well%20as%20downstream%20water%20use%20(e.g.,%20use%20of%20water%20for%20consumer%20products,%20such%20as%20soaps,%20shampoos,%20and%20cleaning%20solutions).%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20clause%201.2.2%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3ETo%20identify%20catchments%20where%20it%20causes%20water-related%20impacts,%20the%20organization%20can%20use%20global%20catchment%20data%20sets.%20These%20include%20the%20CEO%20Water%20Mandate%20&apos;Interactive%20Database%20of%20the%20World&apos;s%20River%20Basins&apos;1,%20and%20the%20WWF%20&apos;HydroSHEDS&apos;2.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3EGuidance%20for%20Disclosure%20303-2%20%3C/span%3E%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EMinimum%20standards%20are%20those%20that%20go%20beyond%20regulatory%20requirements%20in%20controlling%20the%20quality%20of%20effluent%20discharge.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EWater%20quality%20refers%20to%20the%20physical,%20chemical,%20biological,%20and%20taste-related%20characteristics%20of%20water.%20It%20is%20a%20measure%20of%20water%20suitability%20for%20a%20given%20purpose%20or%20function,%20including%20its%20use%20as%20a%20human%20right.%20Water%20quality%20standards%20help%20uphold%20water%20quality%20in%20order%20to%20protect%20ecosystems,%20wildlife,%20and%20human%20health%20and%20welfare,%20and%20can%20be%20based%20on%20water%20properties,%20such%20as%20temperature%20or%20pH%20value.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20specific%20choice%20of%20water%20quality%20standards%20and%20parameters%20can%20vary%20depending%20on%20an%20organization&amp;rsquo;s%20products,%20services,%20and%20facility%20locations,%20and%20can%20depend%20on%20national%20and/or%20regional%20regulations,%20as%20well%20as%20the%20profile%20of%20the%20receiving%20waterbody.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EBackground%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20volume%20of%20water%20withdrawal%20from%20areas%20with%20water%20stress%20can%20indicate%20an%20organization&amp;rsquo;s%20impacts%20in%20sensitive%20locations.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3ETo%20learn%20more%20about%20locations%20where%20water-related%20impacts%20might%20be%20significant,%20and%20where%20actions%20to%20address%20them%20are%20most%20needed,%20the%20reporting%20organization%20can%20also%20report%20the%20information%20requested%20in%20Disclosure%20303-3%20for%20each%20facility%20in%20areas%20with%20water%20stress.%20This%20can%20give%20stakeholders%20more%20confidence%20in%20the%20organization&amp;rsquo;s%20water%20stewardship%20efforts%20and%20practices.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20%3Cstrong%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%20background-color:%20initial;%22%3E&amp;amp;%20Compilation%20requirement%3C/strong%3E%20for%20Disclosure%20303-3%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EFor%20an%20example%20of%20how%20to%20present%20information%20on%20requirements%20in%20Disclosure%20303-3,%20see%20Table%201.%20Surface%20water%20includes%20collected%20or%20harvested%20rainwater.%20Third-party%20water%20includes%20water%20supplied%20by%20municipal%20water%20networks%20or%20other%20organizations.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3ECompilation%20requirements%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.1%20When%20compiling%20the%20information%20specified%20in%20Disclosure%20303-3,%20the%20reporting%20organization%20shall%20use%20publicly%20available%20and%20credible%20tools%20and%20methodologies%20for%20assessing%20water%20stress%20in%20an%20area.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20Guidance%20for%20Disclosure%20303-3-b%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EWater%20stress%20refers%20to%20the%20ability,%20or%20lack%20thereof,%20to%20meet%20the%20human%20and%20ecological%20demand%20for%20water.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EWater%20stress%20can%20refer%20to%20the%20availability,%20quality,%20or%20accessibility%20of%20water.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EPublicly%20available%20and%20credible%20tools%20for%20assessing%20areas%20with%20water%20stress%20include%20the%20World%20Resources%20Institute%20&amp;lsquo;Aqueduct%20Water%20Risk%20Atlas,&apos;%20and%20the%20WWF%20&apos;Water%20Risk%20Filter&apos;.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EBased%20on%20these%20tools,%20water%20stress%20in%20an%20area%20may%20be%20assessed%20using%20either%20of%20the%20following%20indicators%20and%20their%20thresholds:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;bull;%20The%20ratio%20of%20total%20annual%20water%20withdrawal%20to%20total%20available%20annual%20renewable%20water%20supply%20(i.e.,%20baseline%20water%20stress)%20is%20high%20(40-80%25)%20or%20extremely%20high%20(&amp;gt;80%25)3;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;bull;%20The%20ratio%20of%20water%20consumption-to-availability%20(i.e.,%20water%20depletion)%20is%20moderate%20(dry-year%20depletion,%20where%20for%20at%20least%2010%25%20of%20the%20time,%20the%20monthly%20depletion%20ratio%20is%20&amp;gt;75%25),%20high%20(seasonal%20depletion,%20where%20for%20one%20month%20of%20the%20year%20on%20average,%20the%20depletion%20ratio%20is%20&amp;gt;75%25),%20or%20very%20high%20(ongoing%20depletion,%20where%20the%20depletion%20ratio%20on%20average%20is%20&amp;gt;75%25)4.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20may%20use%20these%20indicators%20even%20though%20they%20account%20only%20for%20quantity%20and%20not%20the%20quality%20or%20accessibility%20of%20water%20as%20per%20the%20inclusive%20approach%20to%20the%20definition%20of%20water%20stress.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20can%20complement%20the%20results%20from%20these%20tools%20with%20their%20own%20assessments,%20to%20provide%20more%20granular%20local-level%20data.%20Water%20stress%20in%20an%20area%20may%20be%20measured%20at%20catchment%20level%20at%20a%20minimum.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20Guidance%20for%20Disclosure%20303-3-b-v%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EIf%20water%20is%20supplied%20by%20a%20third%20party,%20the%20organization%20is%20required%20to%20request%20information%20about%20its%20withdrawal%20sources,%20listed%20in%20Disclosures%20303-3-b-i%20to%20303-3-b-iv,%20from%20the%20third-party%20water%20supplier.%3Cspan%20style=%22background-color:%20initial;%20font-size:%200.8125rem;%22%3EThe%20organization%20can%20report%20any%20additional%20information%20about%20third-party%20water,%20such%20as%20who%20the%20third-party%20water%20suppliers%20are%20and%20the%20volume%20of%20water%20supplied%20by%20them.%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20Disclosure%20303-3-c%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20is%20required%20to%20provide%20a%20breakdown%20of%20the%20water%20withdrawn%20from%20each%20of%20the%20sources%20listed%20in%20Disclosures%20303-3-a%20and%20303-3-b%20(surface%20water,%20groundwater,%20seawater,%20produced%20water,%20third-party%20water)%20by%20the%20categories%20freshwater%20and%20other%20water.%20The%20organization%20is%20only%20required%20to%20provide%20this%20breakdown%20for%20the%20sources%20it%20has%20withdrawn%20water%20from.%20If%20all%20water%20withdrawn%20from%20a%20source%20belongs%20only%20to%20one%20category%20(i.e.,%20to%20freshwater%20or%20to%20other%20water),%20the%20organization%20can%20report%20the%20volume%20for%20the%20remaining%20category%20as%20zero.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EFor%20example,%20if%20all%20the%20withdrawn%20seawater%20belongs%20to%20the%20other%20water%20category,%20the%20organization%20can%20report%20the%20volume%20of%20freshwater%20under%20this%20source%20as%20zero.%20Other%20water%20constitutes%20any%20water%20that%20has%20a%20concentration%20of%20total%20dissolved%20solids%20higher%20than%201,000%20mg/L.%20Other%20water%20is%20therefore%20all%20water%20that%20does%20not%20fall%20into%20the%20freshwater%20category.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20is,%20at%20a%20minimum,%20required%20to%20report%20a%20figure%20for%20other%20water%20withdrawal%20for%20each%20of%20the%20sources%20listed%20in%20Disclosures%20303-3-a%20and%20303-3-b.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20can%20additionally%20report%20any%20further%20breakdowns%20for%20other%20water%20withdrawal%20based%20on%20its%20water%20management%20and%20reporting%20practices,%20as%20long%20as%20it%20explains%20the%20approach%20used%20to%20define%20water%20quality%20using%20Disclosure%20303-3-d.%20The%20organization%20can%20report%20additional%20information%20on%20how%20water%20quality%20has%20been%20determined,%20including%20consideration%20of%20the%20potential%20value%20of%20water%20to%20its%20users,%20as%20well%20as%20any%20absolute%20physical%20and/or%20chemical%20criteria%20used.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20Guidance%20for%20clause%202.2.1%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3ETo%20compile%20this%20information,%20the%20organization%20can%20use%20the%20following%20approach:%20(a)%20determine%20which%20facilities%20are%20located%20in%20areas%20with%20water%20stress,%20(b)%20for%20each%20of%20these%20facilities,%20report%20a%20breakdown%20of%20the%20total%20water%20withdrawal%20by%20surface%20water,%20groundwater,%20seawater,%20produced%20water,%20and%20third-party%20water.%20For%20an%20example%20of%20how%20to%20present%20this%20information,%20see%20Table%202.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20clause%202.2.2%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3ETo%20compile%20this%20information,%20the%20organization%20can%20use%20the%20following%20approach:%20(a)%20determine%20which%20suppliers%20are%20located%20in%20areas%20with%20water%20stress,%20(b)%20determine%20which%20of%20these%20suppliers%20cause%20significant%20water-related%20impacts,%20(c)%20add%20up%20the%20total%20water%20withdrawal%20of%20each%20of%20these%20suppliers,%20(d)%20report%20the%20sum.%20For%20an%20example%20of%20how%20to%20present%20this%20information,%20see%20Table%203.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EBackground%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EQuantifying%20the%20volume%20of%20water%20discharge%20can%20help%20an%20organization%20understand%20its%20negative%20impacts%20on%20the%20receiving%20waterbody.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20relationship%20between%20water%20discharge%20and%20negative%20impacts%20is%20not%20linear.%20An%20increase%20in%20the%20total%20volume%20of%20water%20discharge%20does%20not%20necessarily%20correspond%20to%20greater%20negative%20impacts,%20since%20these%20impacts%20depend%20on%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20water%20discharge%20and%20the%20sensitivity%20of%20the%20receiving%20waterbody.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EAn%20organization%20with%20a%20high%20volume%20of%20water%20discharge,%20but%20also%20a%20high%20level%20of%20treatment%20and%20strict%20quality%20standards,%20can%20have%20positive%20impacts%20on%20the%20receiving%20waterbody.%20To%20learn%20more%20about%20locations%20where%20water-related%20impacts%20might%20be%20significant,%20and%20where%20actions%20to%20address%20them%20are%20most%20needed,%20the%20reporting%20organization%20can%20also%20report%20the%20information%20requested%20in%20Disclosure%20303-4%20for%20each%20facility%20in%20areas%20with%20water%20stress.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20%3Cstrong%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%20background-color:%20initial;%22%3E&amp;amp;%20Compilation%20requirement%3C/strong%3E%20for%20Disclosure%20303-4%3C/strong%3E%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EFor%20an%20example%20of%20how%20to%20present%20information%20on%20requirements%20in%20Disclosure%20303-4,%20see%20Table%201.%20See%20Guidance%20for%20Disclosure%20303-3-b%20for%20how%20to%20assess%20areas%20with%20water%20stress.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3ECompilation%20requirements%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.3%20When%20compiling%20the%20information%20specified%20in%20Disclosure%20303-4,%20the%20reporting%20organization%20shall%20use%20publicly%20available%20and%20credible%20tools%20and%20methodologies%20for%20assessing%20water%20stress%20in%20an%20area.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20Guidance%20for%20Disclosure%20303-4-a-iv%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EAn%20example%20of%20third-party%20water%20discharge%20is%20when%20an%20organization%20sends%20water%20and%20effluents%20to%20other%20organizations%20for%20use.%20In%20these%20instances,%20the%20organization%20is%20required%20to%20report%20the%20volume%20of%20this%20water%20discharge%20separately.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20Guidance%20for%20Disclosures%20303-4-b%20and%20303-4-c%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20is%20required%20to%20provide%20a%20breakdown%20of%20the%20water%20discharged%20to%20all%20areas%20and%20to%20all%20areas%20with%20water%20stress%20by%20the%20categories%20freshwater%20and%20other%20water.%20Other%20water%20constitutes%20any%20water%20that%20has%20a%20concentration%20of%20total%20dissolved%20solids%20higher%20than%201,000%20mg/L.%20Other%20water%20is%20therefore%20all%20water%20that%20does%20not%20fall%20into%20the%20freshwater%20category.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20is,%20at%20a%20minimum,%20required%20to%20report%20a%20figure%20for%20other%20water%20discharged.%20The%20organization%20can%20additionally%20report%20any%20further%20breakdowns%20for%20other%20water%20discharge%20based%20on%20its%20water%20management%20and%20reporting%20practices,%20as%20long%20as%20it%20explains%20the%20approach%20used%20to%20define%20water%20quality%20using%20Disclosure%20303-4-e.%20The%20organization%20can%20report%20additional%20information%20on%20how%20water%20quality%20has%20been%20determined,%20including%20consideration%20of%20the%20potential%20value%20of%20water%20to%20its%20users,%20as%20well%20as%20any%20absolute%20physical%20and/or%20chemical%20criteria%20used.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20Guidance%20for%20Disclosure%20303-4-d%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EIn%20the%20context%20of%20this%20Standard,%20substances%20of%20concern%20are%20those%20that%20cause%20irreversible%20damage%20to%20the%20waterbody,%20ecosystem,%20or%20human%20health.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EDischarge%20limits%20for%20substances%20of%20concern%20can%20be%20based%20on%20regulation%20and/or%20other%20factors%20determined%20by%20an%20organization.%20In%20countries%20where%20no%20regulations%20for%20discharge%20limits%20are%20available,%20the%20organization%20can%20develop%20its%20own%20discharge%20limits.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;lsquo;Discharge%20consent&amp;rsquo;%20is%20the%20permission%20granted%20to%20an%20organization,%20allowing%20it%20to%20discharge%20a%20set%20amount%20of%20a%20substance.%20The%20organization%20can%20report%20any%20unauthorized%20discharges%20that%20exceed%20these%20limits%20using%20Disclosure%20303-4-d.%20The%20organization%20can%20also%20describe%20any%20plans%20to%20reduce%20unauthorized%20discharges%20in%20the%20future.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20Guidance%20for%20clause%202.4.2%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EReporting%20water%20discharge%20by%20level%20of%20treatment%20can%20provide%20insight%20into%20the%20effort%20an%20organization%20is%20making%20to%20improve%20the%20quality%20of%20its%20water%20discharge.%20When%20reporting%20how%20the%20treatment%20levels%20were%20determined,%20the%20organization%20is%20expected%20to%20include%20the%20reasons%20why%20a%20certain%20level%20of%20treatment%20was%20set.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20level%20of%20treatment%20can%20be%20reported%20for%20any%20water%20or%20effluents%20at%20the%20point%20of%20discharge,%20whether%20treated%20by%20the%20organization%20onsite%20or%20sent%20to%20a%20third%20party%20for%20treatment.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EWater%20treatment%20involves%20physical,%20chemical%20or%20biological%20processes%20that%20improve%20water%20quality%20by%20removing%20solids,%20pollutants,%20and%20organic%20matter%20from%20water%20and%20effluents.%20Minimum%20requirements%20for%20treatment%20might%20be%20specified%20in%20national,%20state,%20or%20local%20legislation;%20however,%20the%20organization%20is%20expected%20to%20consider%20its%20overall%20water%20discharge%20impacts%20and%20the%20needs%20of%20other%20water%20users%20in%20setting%20treatment%20levels.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20can%20break%20down%20its%20water%20discharge%20by%20the%20following%20treatment%20levels:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;bull;%20Primary%20treatment,%20which%20aims%20to%20remove%20solid%20substances%20that%20settle%20or%20float%20on%20the%20water%20surface;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;bull;%20Secondary%20treatment,%20which%20aims%20to%20remove%20substances%20and%20materials%20that%20have%20remained%20in%20the%20water,%20or%20are%20dissolved%20or%20suspended%20in%20it;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;bull;%20Tertiary%20treatment,%20which%20aims%20to%20upgrade%20water%20to%20a%20higher%20level%20of%20quality%20before%20it%20is%20discharged.%20It%20includes%20processes%20that%20remove,%20for%20example,%20heavy%20metals,%20nitrogen,%20and%20phosphorus.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EAn%20organization%20might%20withdraw%20and%20discharge%20water%20of%20good%20quality%20that%20does%20not%20require%20treatment.%20If%20so,%20the%20organization%20can%20explain%20this%20in%20its%20reported%20information.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&amp;nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20Guidance%20for%20clause%202.4.3%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EMinimum%20standards%20are%20those%20that%20go%20beyond%20regulatory%20requirements%20in%20controlling